==English==
===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]]: /li/

===Suffix===
'''-ly'''

#Used to form [[adverb]]s from [[adjective]]s.
#:''[[suddenly]]''
#Used to form [[adjective]]s from [[noun]]s, the adjectives having the sense of "like or characteristic of what is denoted by the noun".
#:''[[gentlemanly]]''

*Note: Usage 2 derives from Old English 'līc', meaning 'body'.  It is still found as a [[bound morpheme]] in Modern English.
*:E.g. frēond-līc 'friendly' (lit. friend-like, having the appearance of a friend)

====Translations====
*French: (1): [[-ment]]
*Italian: (1): [[-mente]]

